  <main>
    <h1>What Is Web Development?</h1>
    <p>
      Web development is the process of building websites that people can visit in a browser.
      Most pages are created using three main technologies: <strong>HTML</strong>, <strong>CSS</strong>, and <strong>JavaScript</strong>.
    </p>
    <h2>HTML</h2>
    <p>
      HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the structure of a page.
      It uses tags like <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;p&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> to mark headings, paragraphs, and links.
    </p>
    <h2>CSS</h2>
    <p>
      CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) controls how the page looks.
      With CSS you can change colors, fonts, spacing, and layout.
    </p>
    <h2>JavaScript</h2>
    <p>
      JavaScript adds interactivity.
      For example, in this project JavaScript is used to check the quiz answers and show the score.
    </p>
    <p>
      After reading this page and the Resources page, you can try the quiz to see how much you remember.
    </p>
  </main>

